title: How to Make Easy Peach Cobbler

steps.headline: Spray pan with non-stick spray or smear with oil.
Open can(s) of peaches and pour into bottom of pan (juice and all).
Pour cake mix on top of peaches.
steps.description: Spread evenly and break up big pieces.

steps.headline: Cut butter into slices (about 14-16 pieces per stick).
Place butter pieces evenly on top of cake mix evenly.

text: Preheat oven to 350ºF/175ºC.  Spray pan with non-stick spray or smear with oil.  Open can(s) of peaches and pour into bottom of pan (juice and all). Evenly spread peaches. Pour cake mix on top of peaches. Spread evenly and break up big pieces. Cut butter into slices (about 14-16 pieces per stick).  Place butter pieces evenly on top of cake mix evenly.  Cook for 1 hour until brown.  Finished.
